%erg v1
Title: Enforce erg source read-only in IDH; edits must go to git-erg project
Created: 2026-04-30
Author: claude

--- log ---
2026-04-30T07:30Z claude created

--- body ---
## Context

The `erg` Go source lives in the git-erg project. IDH carries a vendored copy
at `tickets/tools/go/` (source) and `tickets/tools/go/erg` (compiled binary,
gitignored). Agents working on IDH tickets have no reason to edit the Go source —
but nothing currently prevents them from doing so. An accidental edit to
`tickets/tools/go/` in IDH would diverge the vendored source from the canonical
git-erg version with no cross-repo tracking.

The intended invariant: **IDH is a consumer of erg, not a developer of it.**
All erg source changes must be made in the git-erg repo and pulled into IDH
via a deliberate update step.

This is a separate concern from ticket 0057 (which routes `.erg` file mutations
through the erg binary). This ticket is about protecting the erg Go *source code*
in IDH from unintended modification.

## Actions

1. **Add a pre-commit hook in IDH** that rejects any staged change to
   `tickets/tools/go/**`. Error message: "erg source is read-only in IDH —
   commit changes to git-erg project instead."

2. **Wire the hook** in `.git/hooks/pre-commit` (or via the existing hook
   infrastructure in `scripts/`). Ensure it runs in CI (`validate-tickets` job
   or new job).

3. **Document the update path.** Add a section to `scripts/` or `README` that
   describes how to pull a new erg binary from git-erg into IDH:
   ```
   cd /path/to/git-erg && go build -o /path/to/idh/tickets/tools/go/erg .
   ```
   Or, if the binary is distributed as a release artifact, document the download
   step.

4. **Remove erg source from IDH (stretch goal).** If the Go source is only
   present to allow local builds, consider removing it entirely and relying solely
   on the pre-built binary. This eliminates the read-only problem by removing the
   source. Keep `tickets/tools/go/erg` (binary) but delete `tickets/tools/go/*.go`.

## Test

- Stage a dummy change to `tickets/tools/go/main.go` in IDH. Attempt commit.
  Verify hook blocks it with the correct error message.
- Confirm no existing CI workflow is broken by the hook.

## Exit criteria

- Pre-commit hook in IDH blocks any commit touching `tickets/tools/go/**` (except
  the binary itself, which is gitignored).
- Hook message clearly directs the developer to git-erg.
- CI enforces the same constraint.
